The WPA400 meter signal might have been interrupted one way or the other, but the lockdown is ongoing, so it’s not like my plan for quarantine is to drive long distances or not follow the appropriate sanitary protocol anyway.

What WPA400’s approach has allowed me to get beyond this uncanny contrast of Wallis and Futuna is the switch from a long-term pulse to a long-term signal. The signal is stuck in the range of 2-3%, where the pulse is now a blip of 0.4%. I can tell that it’s happening in Wallis and Futuna not because I can chart my very own breakthrough case between Russia and the Arctic Circle as by scanning for 409KiB wireless connections across the Atlantic, and picking out WPA400-palindromes to plot onto Github’s timeline of a covid-19 world, or by simply recognizing a relative number no matter where it goes. Signal strength bars lower at -102dBm? That stands out, same with WPA-404.

No wonder people buy a car key fob signal booster because this was long before the invention of cell phone signal boosters while you’re trapped in your house. This is a mental social media habit you might have had, where you looked
